---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Beginner's Guide to Source Mechanics - Tower of Fantasy";
const description = "Master Source abilities, understand elemental reactions, and optimize your combat rotation in Tower of Fantasy.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
  <article class="guide">
    <h1>🔮 Beginner's Guide to Source Mechanics</h1>

    <div class="intro">
      <p>Source abilities are the core combat system in Tower of Fantasy. Unlike regular weapon skills, Source abilities are tied to your character's progression and can be used with any weapon. Mastering Source mechanics is essential for high-level content.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="basics">
      <h2>📚 Source Basics</h2>

      <div class="concept-card">
        <h3>What is Source?</h3>
        <p>Source is a mysterious energy that permeates the world of Tower of Fantasy. Your character can harness this energy to perform special abilities that are independent of your equipped weapons.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Source Abilities:</strong> Special skills unlocked through progression</li>
          <li><strong>Source Energy:</strong> Resource that powers these abilities (similar to mana)</li>
          <li><strong>Source Level:</strong> Your overall mastery of Source (increases with use)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="concept-card">
        <h3>How to Unlock Source Abilities</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Complete the Main Quest:</strong> Source abilities are introduced during the early main questline (around level 10-15).</li>
          <li><strong>Visit Source Pillars:</strong> Scattered throughout the world, these pillars teach you new abilities when you interact with them.</li>
          <li><strong>Upgrade with Source Cores:</strong> Find Source Cores (dropped by enemies or found in chests) to level up your abilities.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="elements">
      <h2>🌟 Elemental System</h2>
      <p>Source abilities are tied to 5 elements. Each element has strengths and weaknesses, and combining them creates powerful reactions.</p>

      <table>
        <tr>
          <th>Element</th>
          <th>Icon</th>
          <th>Strengths</th>
          <th>Weakness</th>
          <th>Best For</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Fire</strong></td>
          <td>🔥</td>
          <td>High damage over time</td>
          <td>Water</td>
          <td>Sustained damage, crowd control</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Water</strong></td>
          <td>💧</td>
          <td>Healing, crowd control</td>
          <td>Lightning</td>
          <td>Support, survivability</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Lightning</strong></td>
          <td>⚡</td>
          <td>Burst damage, stun</td>
          <td>Earth</td>
          <td>Quick kills, interrupting enemies</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Earth</strong></td>
          <td>🌍</td>
          <td>Defense, armor breaks</td>
          <td>Fire</td>
          <td>Tanking, breaking enemy shields</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Wind</strong></td>
          <td>🌪️</td>
          <td>Mobility, evasion</td>
          <td>None (neutral)</td>
          <td>Dodging, repositioning</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section class="reactions">
      <h2>💥 Elemental Reactions</h2>
      <p>When you apply two different elements to an enemy, they react. These reactions deal bonus damage and apply status effects.</p>

      <div class="reaction-grid">
        <div class="reaction-card">
          <h3>🔥 + 💧 = Steam</h3>
          <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Reduces enemy defense by 30% for 10 seconds</p>
          <p><strong>Best Use:</strong> Apply before burst damage windows</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reaction-card">
          <h3>💧 + ⚡ = Electro-Charged</h3>
          <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Stuns the enemy for 3 seconds</p>
          <p><strong>Best Use:</strong> Interrupting boss attacks or escaping dangerous situations</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reaction-card">
          <h3>⚡ + 🌍 = Crystallize</h3>
          <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Creates a shield that absorbs damage equal to 20% of your max HP</p>
          <p><strong>Best Use:</strong> Defensive situations, tanking boss mechanics</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reaction-card">
          <h3>🌍 + 🔥 = Melt</h3>
          <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Deals 150% bonus damage and breaks enemy shields instantly</p>
          <p><strong>Best Use:</strong> Against shielded enemies or bosses</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reaction-card">
          <h3>🔥 + 🌪️ = Overheat</h3>
          <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Applies burning + increases movement speed by 20% for 8 seconds</p>
          <p><strong>Best Use:</strong> Kiting enemies, hit-and-run tactics</p>
        </div>

        <div class="reaction-card">
          <h3>💧 + 🌪️ = Frost</h3>
          <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Slows enemy movement speed by 50% for 12 seconds</p>
          <p><strong>Best Use:</strong> Crowd control, slowing fast enemies</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tip-box">
        <strong>💡 Pro Tip:</strong> Some reactions are better than others. Steam (Fire + Water) and Melt (Earth + Fire) are the highest damage. Prioritize these for DPS builds.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="abilities">
      <h2>🎯 Essential Source Abilities</h2>

      <div class="ability-card">
        <h3>🔥 Flame Burst (Fire)</h3>
        <p><strong>Unlock:</strong> Level 10, Fire Source Pillar</p>
        <p><strong>Cooldown:</strong> 8 seconds</p>
        <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Launches a fireball that explodes on impact, dealing AoE damage and applying Burn for 5 seconds.</p>
        <p><strong>Upgrade Priority:</strong> ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (Core damage ability)</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ability-card">
        <h3>💧 Healing Wave (Water)</h3>
        <p><strong>Unlock:</strong> Level 12, Water Source Pillar</p>
        <p><strong>Cooldown:</strong> 15 seconds</p>
        <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Heals yourself and nearby allies for 30% of max HP. Removes one debuff.</p>
        <p><strong>Upgrade Priority:</strong> ⭐⭐⭐⭐ (Essential for survivability)</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ability-card">
        <h3>⚡ Lightning Strike (Lightning)</h3>
        <p><strong>Unlock:</strong> Level 15, Lightning Source Pillar</p>
        <p><strong>Cooldown:</strong> 10 seconds</p>
        <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Calls down lightning on a target area, dealing high burst damage and stunning enemies for 2 seconds.</p>
        <p><strong>Upgrade Priority:</strong> ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (Best single-target damage)</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ability-card">
        <h3>🌍 Earth Shield (Earth)</h3>
        <p><strong>Unlock:</strong> Level 18, Earth Source Pillar</p>
        <p><strong>Cooldown:</strong> 20 seconds</p>
        <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Creates a shield that absorbs damage equal to 50% of max HP for 10 seconds. While active, increases attack power by 20%.</p>
        <p><strong>Upgrade Priority:</strong> ⭐⭐⭐ (Situational, but great for tough fights)</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ability-card">
        <h3>🌪️ Wind Dash (Wind)</h3>
        <p><strong>Unlock:</strong> Level 8, Wind Source Pillar</p>
        <p><strong>Cooldown:</strong> 6 seconds</p>
        <p><strong>Effect:</strong> Dashes forward a short distance, dealing damage to enemies in your path. Grants 2 seconds of invincibility frames.</p>
        <p><strong>Upgrade Priority:</strong> ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ (Mobility is essential)</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="rotation">
      <h2>⚔️ Optimal Combat Rotation</h2>
      <p>Here's how to combine Source abilities for maximum effectiveness:</p>

      <div class="rotation-card">
        <h3>🎯 Opening Rotation (First 5 Seconds)</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Wind Dash</strong> → Close distance and apply Wind element</li>
          <li><strong>Flame Burst</strong> → Apply Fire element, triggering Overheat (damage + speed boost)</li>
          <li><strong>Lightning Strike</strong> → Burst damage on the primary target</li>
          <li><strong>Basic attacks</strong> → Fill time while cooldowns reset</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="rotation-card">
        <h3>🛡️ Defensive Rotation (When Taking Heavy Damage)</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Earth Shield</strong> → Absorb incoming damage</li>
          <li><strong>Wind Dash</strong> → Reposition away from danger</li>
          <li><strong>Healing Wave</strong> → Recover HP and remove debuffs</li>
          <li><strong>Continue dodging</strong> → Use regular dodge rolls until abilities are ready</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="rotation-card">
        <h3>💥 Burst Rotation (For Boss Fights)</h3>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Flame Burst</strong> → Apply Fire element</li>
          <li><strong>Healing Wave</strong> → Apply Water element, triggering Steam (defense reduction)</li>
          <li><strong>Lightning Strike</strong> → Burst damage during the defense debuff window</li>
          <li><strong>Earth Shield</strong> → Activate for the +20% attack power bonus</li>
          <li><strong>Weapon skills</strong> → Unload your strongest weapon attacks</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tips">
      <h2>💡 Pro Tips</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Element stacking matters.</strong> Apply elements in the right order to get the reaction you want. Fire first, then Water = Steam. Reversing the order wastes the reaction.</li>
        <li><strong>Don't neglect Wind Dash.</strong> It's not just for damage — the invincibility frames can save you from lethal attacks.</li>
        <li><strong>Healing Wave removes debuffs.</strong> If you're poisoned or burned, use it immediately. The heal is secondary to the cleanse.</li>
        <li><strong>Upgrade defensively first.</strong> Early game, prioritize Healing Wave and Earth Shield. You can always deal damage later, but you can't recover from a one-shot.</li>
        <li><strong>Source Cores are valuable.</strong> Don't waste them on abilities you don't use. Focus on 3-4 core abilities and max them out.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="progression">
      <h2>📈 Progression Path</h2>
      <p>Here's the recommended order for unlocking and upgrading Source abilities:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Level 8:</strong> Unlock Wind Dash (mobility is essential)</li>
        <li><strong>Level 10:</strong> Unlock Flame Burst (basic damage)</li>
        <li><strong>Level 12:</strong> Unlock Healing Wave (survivability)</li>
        <li><strong>Level 15:</strong> Unlock Lightning Strike (burst damage)</li>
        <li><strong>Level 18:</strong> Unlock Earth Shield (optional, situational)</li>
        <li><strong>Level 20+:</strong> Upgrade Flame Burst and Lightning Strike first</li>
        <li><strong>Level 25+:</strong> Upgrade Healing Wave and Wind Dash</li>
        <li><strong>Level 30+:</strong> Max out all abilities</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <div class="final-note">
      <h2>🎯 Final Thoughts</h2>
      <p>Source abilities are what separate beginner players from veterans. Master the elemental reactions, optimize your rotation, and you'll see a massive improvement in your combat effectiveness. Don't neglect them — they're just as important as your weapons and gear.</p>
      <p><strong>Next step:</strong> Check out our <a href="/tower-of-fantasy/team-comps">Team Compositions Guide</a> to learn how to build a team that complements your Source abilities.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .guide {
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .intro {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .concept-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #4a90d9;
  }

  .reaction-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .reaction-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
  }

  .reaction-card h3 {
    border: none;
    margin-top: 0;
    color: #ffc107;
  }

  .ability-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #4a90d9;
  }

  .rotation-card {
    background: #f9f9f9;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #dc3545;
  }

  .tip-box {
    background: #d4edda;
    padding: 1rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-left: 4px solid #28a745;
  }

  .final-note {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e 0%, #16213e 100%);
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .final-note h2 {
    color: #4a90d9;
    border: none;
  }

  .final-note a {
    color: #4a90d9;
  }
</style>
